    @ModelExternalEvents(imported={Start.class,Stop.class,Refill.class,GeneratorRequiredPowerChanged.class},
                     exported={TankEmpty.class,TankNoLongerEmpty.class})
 @ModelImportedVariable(name="generatorOutputPower",
                       type=java.lang.Double.class)
public class GeneratorFuelModel
extends fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.hioa.models.AtomicHIOA
implements GeneratorStateManagementI
    The class GeneratorFuelModel implements the simulation model for the fuel consumption of the generator.

    Description

    • Imported events: Start, Stop, Refill, GeneratorRequiredPowerChanged
    • Exported events: TankEmpty, TankNoLongerEmpty
    • Imported variables: name = generatorOutputPower, type = Double
    • Exported variables: none

    Implementation Invariants

     invariant       !currentLevel.isInitialised() || (currentLevel.getValue() >= 0.0 && currentLevel.getValue() < maxCapacity)
 invariant       !lastDerivative.isInitialised() || (lastDerivative.getValue() <= 0.0)
 invariant       standardLevelQuantum > 0.0
 invariant       Math.abs(currentLevelQuantum) >= 0.0 && Math.abs(currentLevelQuantum <= standardLevelQuantum)

    Invariants

     invariant       TimeUnit.HOURS.equals(GlobalSimulationConfigurationI.TIME_UNIT)

    Created on : 2025-10-28

    Author:
    Jacques Malenfant

      • computeFuelLevelDerivative

        protected double computeFuelLevelDerivative()
        compute the current derivative of the fuel level in MeasurementUnit.LITERS/h.

        Description

        The generator has a minimal and a maximal fuel consumption (derivative of the fuel level) corresponding to the idle state or the minimal power production for the former and the maximal power production for the latter. The model assumes that between these two ends, the fuel consumption grows linearly, proportionally to the power production. The result is always negative or 0, as the fuel level goes down while producing.

        Contract

         pre     true        // no precondition.
 post    return <= 0.0
        Returns:
        the current derivative of the fuel level.
